node.text:
Welcome to my life. 
@thedailyliving Ep.02
Follow for WEEKLY episodes, 
Uploaded Monday’s 7AM on YouTube (link in bio)
And Thursday 6PM on Instagram (follow me) We just getting started!

My name is Alex Hayes &  I am 21 years old from Sydney. Entertaining is my passion - I will also do anything that gets my heart pumping. I believe in pushing the Mind & Body to overcome anything. Life shouldn't be taken too seriously, but life also shouldn't be taken for granted -  i want to inspire everyone to overcome self doubt & follow what makes them happy. 
These episodes are just a documentation of my life and what i love doing.

node.text:
Going through the camera roll this morning & was smiling at all the amazing memories & good times that I’ve had. So i had a thought, While im injured and limited to what i can do physically, im gonna post some of my favourite memories on Reels from the past few years that i either haven’t shared or old content thats forgotten about that gets me pumped. 
This was a super fun trip with some great friends down the south coast of Australia at the very beginning of last year!! Will forever be a trip for the books 📚 #LIVEDAILYREELS

node.text:
Can’t wait to be back in the water doing the ocean dance 🏄🏻‍♂️ 
This surf was a few months ago & was one of my first surfs after my back to back shoulder AC joint injuries ( on both shoulders 🤣) fuck it’s been a tough year dealing with not being able to perform physically at 100%… certainly been a mental battle for me with how active my lifestyle is & wanting to always push my limits but i Im completely aware that these things happen when you play dangerous games. This is what i live for! I love the risk of putting everything on the edge for the joy of being in the moment. 

I read a quote recently, it was along the lines of “adversity introduces a man to himself” & i couldn’t agree more. The things in life that hurt, are there to instruct! I keep reminding myself that no strength is easily gained!
Im built for this shit - all these problems are just forced opportunities to get stronger. Im extremely grateful for the fun few months of doing activities in between these adversities & i can’t stop dreaming about getting myself stronger & healthier everyday to get back out there doing what i love and pushing my body & mind to places i believe is possible. but mostly, im just pumped to have a fucking good time with whatever i do. Life is too short to leave passions behind. 
I Encourage you to get outside (or inside) & do the things you love in this life because in this crazy world nothing is promised. Do what you love daily & you will live daily.

For now I’m back to square one. focusing on my ankle to get back out there & keep going! Lets goooo
Thanks for the shots @18secondsmagazine
